package.name: Solar
package.summary: Simple object library and application repository for PHP.
package.description:
Solar is a class library and application component suite for PHP 5 (and is PHP5 E_STRICT compliant). Solar provides simple, easy-to-comprehend classes and components for the common aspects of web-based rapid application development.
Solar is designed for developers who intend to distribute their applications to the whole world. This means, for example, the database driver functions work exactly the same way for each supported database. It also means that localization support is built in from the start.
Please visit http://solarphp.com/ for more information.

release.notes:
* Removed classes
* Solar_Test_Assert, moved functionality to Solar_Test
* Added classes
* Solar_Test
* Solar_Test_Suite
* Solar_User_Access and related drivers: Open, None, File (still need Sql, Ini, etc)
* General
* Changed testing methodology away from .phpt to something more like SimpleTest/PHPUnit ... Solar_Test.
* Added many new tests, e.g. for Solar_Sql and the drivers.
* Solar_App
* Adds default _preAction() method to check user privileges for the page-class and action
* Adds default $errors public property for tracking page errors
* Solar_Test_Example
* Moved support class methods out of test files and into the example class (e.g., validation and filter callbacks)
* Solar_Sql
* BC BREAK: createIndex() now takes params $table, $name, $unique (true/false), and $cols (array of col names) ... previously, took $table, $name, $info.
* BC BREAK: query() now always returns boolean true for schema manipulation commands (CREATE, ALTER, DROP) ... this is to hide inconsistencies in how backends report "number of rows affected".
* Bugfix: query() now honors the array binding-data properly.
* Bugfix: select('statement') now works properly (typo).
* Bugfix: createSequence() now works properly (was passing $this instead of $name).
* Bugfix: addColumn now works properly (was omitting the column name in the command).
* Solar_Sql_Driver_*
* Added driver-specific dropIndex() support.
* Solar_Sql_Driver_Mysql::createSequence() now creates sequence tables as InnoDB instead of MyISAM.
* Solar_Sql_Table
* _autoSetup() now massages $this->_idx for proper index info, and uses new Solar_Sql::createIndex() params.
* Solar_Uri
* changed "public function pathEncode()" to "protected function _pathEncode()"
* When auto-discovering the current URI, it adds "example.com" as a dummy host name if $_SERVER['HTTP_HOST'] is empty, then removes it after parsing the URL. This is to avoid notices about parsing errors.
* Solar_User
* Now has public $access property for Solar_User_Access functions
* Solar_View
* Added methods getHelperPath(), getTemplatePath()
* The newHelper() method now properly returns a new standalone helper, instead of re-instantiating the internal copy of that helper. Also, you can now pass a runtime $config as the second parameter.
* Solar_View_Helper_...
* Anchor: now returns just the HREF if no text specified
* Attribs: now skips empty values, returns '' if no attribs found
* Form:
* Now adds 'descr' to all elements
* Removed $_disable and setDisable() (not honored yet)
* Method addFeedback() is now properly fluent (returns $this)
* Added method getStatus()
* FormButton: streamlined output concatenation
* FormOptions: no longer indents the options list
* FormRadio: no longer adds extra newline after first hidden value
* FormSelect: streamlined output concatenation
* Image: loads Solar_View_Helper class now
* LinkStylesheet: adds 'media="screen"' attrib if not otherwise specified
* Style: adds 'media="screen"' attrib if not otherwise specified
* Timestamp default format is now "Y-m-d\TH:i:s".
